					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Much better. One small gripe though:</p> <blockquote> <p>and will attempt to violently attack the responsible party. To date, these instances have been armed with a wide variety of improvised bludgeon and bladed weapons, including crowbars, tire irons, baseball bats, fire axes, and knives.</p> </blockquote> <p>A) &quot;violently attack&quot; feels like a pleonasm<br /> B) Unless you're going to put something in the list of weapons used that's going to make me raise my eyebrows<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-679204-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup>, this doesn't add anything to the article. At least you didn't put a [REDACTED] in there. ;)</p> <p>Still, +1.</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-679204-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. For example: the hindleg of a specimen of <em>B. primigenius</em>, a small child, a gumball vending machine (broken) or a porcelain vase from the Han dynasty</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
